<doc id="1027518" wikidata="Q15229963" url="?curid=1027518" title="Aveleda e Rio de Onor">
<text>Aveleda e Rio de Onor is a civil parish in the municipality of Bragança, Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merging of former parishes Aveleda and Rio de Onor. The population in 2011 was 272, in an area of 106.35 km².

==Language==
Portuguese is spoken by everyone. Historically the main language was Rionorese, an Astur-Leonese language, which is almost extinct today.

== See also ==

* Rihonor de Castilla

